$lang['first_contact_stp34'] = 'Choosing a theme is the first step to customize your Piwigo. Installed themes are listed here.<br>More than one theme can be enabled: users can change their theme by choosing one of the themes enabled here, if the option \'Allow user customization\' is checked on the Option page.';
$lang['first_contact_stp37'] = 'To install new themes, you can directly download them from the tab \'Add a theme\'. Only the themes marked as compatible with your version of Piwigo are shown.<br><br>Let\'s discover plugins now! Click on <em>Plugin » Manage</em>';
$lang['first_contact_stp38'] = 'Plugins are very easy ways to customize your Piwigo. They can do almost anything you can imagine from small text additions to complete features, like the Community plugin which allows non-administrator users to upload without entering the administration part.';
$lang['first_contact_stp39'] = 'The first page lists the installed plugins.<br><br>Activated plugins (currently running plugins) are listed at the top.<br><br>Disabled plugins (installed in the /plugins folder but not activated) are listed at the bottom.<br><br>Deleting a plugin means that any trace of the plugin will be removed (files, options etc). For most plugins, deactivation will keep the data registered by the plugin.';
$lang['first_contact_stp43'] = 'This tour was quite long, but we have seen only a small part of how powerful Piwigo is. Everything has an end, this overview is finished.<br><br>You can investigate more deeply the features of Piwigo by taking another tour or reading our documentation, on the piwigo.org website.<br><br>Don\'t forget also the Help link at the upper right corner of any administration page.<p style="text-align:center">Enjoy your Piwigo!</p>';
